Abstract = {{We develop an all-electron quantum Monte Carlo (QMC) method for solids
   that does not rely on pseudopotentials, and use it to construct a
   primary ultra-high-pressure calibration based on the equation of state
   of cubic boron nitride. We compute the static contribution to the free
   energy with the QMC method and obtain the phonon contribution from
   density functional theory, yielding a high-accuracy calibration up to
   900 GPa usable directly in experiment. We compute the anharmonic Raman
