Abstract = {{We have used density-functional-theory methods to study phases of iron
   at terapascal (TPa) pressures. Hexagonal-close-packed (hcp) iron is
   stable from below 0.1 TPa to multi-TPa pressures, where we find a window
   of 7-21 TPa in which the face-centred-cubic (fcc) phase is slightly more
   stable. At 34 TPa we find a transition to a body-centred-tetragonal
   (bct) phase, which is a small distortion of the body-centred-cubic (bcc)
   structure. The bcc phase also becomes more stable than the hcp above 35
   TPa. The bct and bcc phases become considerably more stable than hcp and
   fcc at even higher pressures, and we expect this result to hold at high
   temperatures.}},
